+TheBirdOfMorning Oh the villains are great in 'The Amazing Spider-Man 2'. 
Or rather, one is. Electro is my favourite superhero villain in years. 
Unlike in others where it is a case of a science experiment going wrong, 
making the character evil uncontrollably, the villain is already 
schizophrenic, and it's a case of what a crazy person would do with this 
power. The 'Electro Suite' music is also brilliant. It's one of my 
faavourite single score tracks as it fits perfectly.

As for Green Goblin, I'm not loving him loads, but he's decent. Unlike in 
other films where the character is developed and comes in at the end as a 
villain, the Green Goblin doesn't die, so it's not like a short lived 
villainous era, and he would have been central in the next film, which I 
would have liked to see.
The transformation scene was also great for him. I didn't think much of it 
the first time I saw it, but when I rewatched it recently I noticed how 
great it was. The music fits perfectly, the flashing lighting is great, and 
the way the body morphs is so disturbing and.. well just a great scene to 
show the creation of a villain.
Electo's transformation was also good - very 'Final Destination'-like. Lots 
of suspense.
Back to Goblin though, the glider was really good, and the costume was 
interesting and unique.

in place for Harry too, but that doesn't bother me any more as given that 
the franchise was supposed to be a trilogy, it makes sense to skip through 
Norman's phase.
